Definition lists are just like ordinary bullet lists, but with
`:` as the marker instead of `-`, `+`, or `*`.  The first
paragraph of the list item is interpreted as the term, and
the rest as the definition.

```
: apple

  red fruit
: banana

  yellow fruit
.
<dl>
<dt>apple</dt>
<dd>
<p>red fruit</p>
</dd>
<dt>banana</dt>
<dd>
<p>yellow fruit</p>
</dd>
</dl>
```

Loose:

```
